title: Tarnation - 2 Albums (4AD)
description:
San Francisco-based Tarnation comprised Paula Frazer (vocals/guitar), Alex Oropeza (guitar), Bill Cuevas (bass/lap steel) and Joe Byrnes (drums).

Using country music as a springboad, Tarnation explored harrowing emotional terrain on their 1995 debut Gentle Creatures. Paula&#039;s stark vocals split the difference between Patsy Cline and Leonard Cohen, while the band&#039;s plaintive twangs and rumbles imbued her songs with an ever-escalating sense of unease.

2 Albums

1. Gentle Creatures, 1995 (4AD)
2. Mirador, 1997 (4AD)
